title: Handley Library, Winchester, Virginia
creator: Highsmith, Carol M., 1946-, photographer
description: Judge John Handley of Scranton, Pa. left $250,000 to open this Public Library. Architects J. Stewart Barney and Henry Otis Chapman of New York designed the building in the Beaux-Arts style. The building opened in 1913, and an addition was added in 1979. A complete renovation designed by Dennis Kowal Architects, was completed in 2001.
